    <note>Cao(1) Bin [8134] Later Zhou dynasty emperor Taizu's consort, Zhang Guifei, was his aunt and his wife was an imperial princess. Cong's [7357] and Wei's [8135] father, Li(2) Zhaoshu's [987] grandfather-in-law. His fourth son Huan's [3876] father-in-law was Li(2) Chuyun's [8073] son, Jilong [3481]. His fifth son, Qi [3869], was Zhao(1) Renzong's [9004] father-in-law. His 12th generation descendants, Wan [3879] and Youwen [3880], died in battle with the Mongols after they had taken Xingzhou(b) in southern Shenxi and were advancing on Daan jun (Sanquan xian), the gate to Sichuan. Du Dagui, 'zhong, ' 43.1a. CBD, 3, 2190-2.</note>
